# ─── Required ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your SimpleMDM API key. Use a read-only key unless you explicitly need writes.
SIMPLEMDM_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# ─── Write actions (off by default) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to true only when you need lock/sync/restart/assign/script actions.
# Use a key scoped to the minimum required permissions before enabling this.
# SIMPLEMDM_ALLOW_WRITES=true

# ─── HTTP behavior (optional — sensible defaults) ────────────────────────────
# Per-request timeout in milliseconds. Requests that exceed this are aborted.
# SIMPLEMDM_TIMEOUT_MS=30000

# Retry count for 429 / 5xx responses. Honors Retry-After when present,
# otherwise exponential backoff.
# SIMPLEMDM_MAX_RETRIES=3

# Safety cap on pagination (all list tools, fleet-analytics tools, resources).
# Each page fetches 100 records, so 200 = 20k max. Raise for very large fleets.
# SIMPLEMDM_MAX_PAGES=200

# In-memory cache TTL in milliseconds (default 5 min). All list endpoints
# and fleet-iteration results are cached; write operations automatically
# invalidate affected entries. Set to 0 to disable caching.
# SIMPLEMDM_CACHE_TTL_MS=300000

# Worker count for fleet-iteration analytics tools (get_top_installed_apps,
# get_app_coverage, get_compliance_violators, etc.). Lower (4) if you see
# 429s; raise (16) only if your tenant tolerates it.
# SIMPLEMDM_FLEET_CONCURRENCY=8

# JSON map of model-prefix -> max-macOS-major. Patches the built-in macOS
# support table used by get_os_eligibility without code changes. Useful when
# Apple ships a new macOS major and you need to update before the next release.
# Example: '{"Mac16,":15,"MacBookPro18,":15}'
# MAC_OS_ELIGIBILITY_OVERRIDE=

# JSON map of currently-shipping OS major per platform. Used as the OS-lag
# baseline by get_compliance_violators (so a single beta device cannot skew
# the result). Update on each Apple major release.
# Example: '{"mac":15,"ios":18,"ipad":18}'
# CURRENT_SUPPORTED_OS_OVERRIDE=

# ─── Future options (not yet supported on the companion app side) ───────────
# Placeholder: integration with Report-SimpleMDM (local app mode) and a
# SimpleMDM-MunkiReport enrichment module is scaffolded in the server code
# but is NOT yet supported by those companion apps. Do not enable these —
# they are listed here only as a pointer for future work. See src/index.ts
# and src/localAppClient.ts for the env var names when/if support lands.
